Place a pan over medium-high heat (without @oil{}).

Once the pan is hot, fry the @chorizo{100%grams} until starting to brown, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

Trim the @salad leaves{120%grams}. Chop or tear into bite-sized pieces.

To make the dressing, mix @balsamic glaze{1%sachet} and @oil{1%tbsp} in a #salad bowl{}.

Halve the @avocado{1%unit} and remove the pit. Cut into chunks while still in its skin. Use a #spoon{} to scoop the flesh into the bowl with the dressing.

Halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%grams} and add to the bowl with the avocado.

Just before serving, toss the salad leaves with the avocado and the dressing. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the dressed salad between #bowls{}.

Top with the chorizo and a crumble of @goat's cheese{100%grams}.

Crack some @black pepper{as desired} onto the salad if desired, as much as you like.

> This recipe is super simple and amazingly delicious too. Salad layered with slightly spicy chorizo and juicy cherry tomatoes. Top that off with creamy avocado and creamier goat's cheese for a tasty, easy breezy lunch.